{{ill|divine rank|lt=Divine rank|ja|神階}}  (神階, Shinkai) is a system of ranking [[kami]] in Shinto. Higher rank meant more lands were given to the shrine and it became wealthier and more powerful.

<ref>{{Cite web |title=Basic Terms of Shinto: Shinkai |url=https://www2.kokugakuin.ac.jp/ijcc/wp/bts/bts_s.html |access-date=2023-11-11 |website=www2.kokugakuin.ac.jp}}</ref>
